    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Age less than 18 years.

          2. Surgery requiring the administration of neuromuscular blocking, agents with planned
             extubation in the postoperative care unit (PACU).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Neuromuscular diseases which may prolong the duration of NMBA's or exaggerate the
             effects of residual blockade.

          2. The need for postoperative mechanical ventilation.

          3. Direct admission to the Pediatric ICU, NICU or CTICU.
      </textblock>
